flowRoot.flowDiv: To use the Interpolate extension, select the paths that you wish to transform, and choose ExtensionsGenerate From PathInterpolate from the menu.

Before invoking the extension, the objects that you are going to transform need to be paths. This is done by selecting the object and using PathObject to Path or Shift+Ctrl+C. If your objects are not paths, the extension will do nothing.

At the time when gradient meshes were not implemented in Inkscape, it was not possible to create a gradient other than linear (straight line) or radial (round).
